name: Work It Out Wombats!
overview: Full of endless energy, Malik, Zadie and Zeke run, bounce, roll and romp, always on the lookout for interesting Treeborhood problems to solve. Malik is thoughtful, considerate and sometimes set in his ways (which can be a good thing when you’re problem-solving). His speedy, adventurous younger sister, Zadie, is a brainstormer extraordinaire, with ideas that range from silly to very smart. Zeke is the youngest sibling — a funny, curious cuddle-bug who loves to play and explore. Super, their grandmother, is the Superintendent and unofficial “Mayor” of the Treeborhood.

episodes.name: Snout and About
episodes.overview: Zadie and Malik retrace their steps to locate Zeke's beloved stuffy Snout.

episodes.name: Zadie's Shell Shuffle
episodes.overview: JunJun's song helps Zadie fix Mr. E's shell garden.

episodes.name: Junior Supers
episodes.overview: The Wombats clean up a big mess.

episodes.name: Measure for Measure
episodes.overview: Measuring helps the Wombats make a new hat for Ellie

episodes.name: Special Delivery
episodes.overview: Zadie helps Malik design a faster route to bring ice cream to a sick Sammy

episodes.name: Campout Confusion
episodes.overview: Zadie tries to host a fun campout.

episodes.name: Snout Wash Day
episodes.overview: Malik makes Snout less stinky.

episodes.name: A Super Recipe
episodes.overview: The Wombats and their friends make a special Thank You treat for Super.

episodes.name: Summerweenie Halloweenie
episodes.overview: The Wombats create a summer version of Halloween

episodes.name: Crab Quakes

episodes.name: Hopping Helpers

episodes.name: The Mighty Zeke
episodes.overview: Zadie tries to help Zeke overcome his fear of riding a two-wheeler.

episodes.name: Gift for a Fish

episodes.overview: After discovering that Super takes an hour for herself every day, the Wombats go on a quest to create the perfect "Me Time."

episodes.overview: The Wombats learn the hard way that you can't keep a talent show in order if all the props are out of order.

episodes.overview: Feeling left out of the Treeborhood's Collection Bonanza, Zeke goes in search of a collection he can call his own.

episodes.overview: Zeke's sorting choices prove interesting when he volunteers to be Mr. E's "Helper for the Day."

episodes.name: Racecar Wombats
episodes.overview: The Wombats are psyched to race in the Treeborhood Derby.

episodes.name: Sparklepants
episodes.overview: Is it possible to have too many pairs of Sparkle Pants?

episodes.overview: After the rain stops, Zadie, Cece, Clyde, and Carly need to find something that's fun for all.

episodes.overview: Mr. E yearns to paint a square, but Quique's lessons aren't helping. Can Zadie's photos bring students to the class to inspire Mr. E?

episodes.name: Super's Super Mug
episodes.overview: Clark and Leah's "Manila in Love" continues.

episodes.name: A Boxful of Snout
episodes.overview: While assisting Mr. E, the Wombats inadvertently "gift-wrapped" Snout. Can they find out which box he's in? Then Zeke laments the absence of Snout, who is accompanying Mr. E on a visit to Aunt Ida. Will a postcard from Snout cure Zeke's depression?

episodes.overview: Harvest Day is being ruined by fog! Can the Wombats save the day by locating Mr. E’s fog goggles, buried in a box somewhere?

episodes.name: The Treeborhood Thankfulness Stew
episodes.overview: It’s time to make the Treeborhood Thankfulness Stew. Can Zeke create a stew that meets Mr. E’s high standards?

episodes.overview: The Flapping Feathers's bus derails on its way to the Parranda. Super fans Sammy and Louisa save the celebration!

episodes.name: Happy New Acorn Year!
episodes.overview: This year, the Wombats can stay up late to watch the New Year's Eve Acorn Drop - if they can keep from falling asleep.

episodes.name: A Room of Our Own
episodes.overview: When Malik and Zadie can't agree on how tidy to keep their bedroom, the solution seems easy. Divide one room between three Wombats!

episodes.name: Zeke's Fairy Village
episodes.overview: It takes a village of Zeke's friends to build enough houses for the "fairies" who have moved in.

episodes.name: A House for Snout
episodes.overview: Zeke and Louisa plan a house for Snout. (They might even get around to building it, if they can manage to stop arguing!)

episodes.name: JunJun's Brain Freeze
episodes.overview: "Hooray for Spring!" is the title of the video Kaya hopes to make ... once JunJun conquers his on-camera jitters.

episodes.name: Treeborhood Carnaval
episodes.overview: While Sammy works to plan a surprise Carnaval for his dad, Quique plans a surprise treat for his son.

episodes.name: Magic Tricky
episodes.overview: Raise the curtain - Malik the Magnificent is about to perform a magic trick! (If he can get it to work, that is).

episodes.name: Malik Gets Muddy
episodes.overview: Malik enters the Undergroundberhood to retrieve JunJun's favorite ball.

episodes.overview: Super hunts for a lost sticker while the wombats collaborate on a new ending for an old Sticker Monster Story.

episodes.name: Count to 10!
episodes.overview: The wombats help Zeke count to 10.

episodes.name: Yo-Ho-Ho: A Sandwich for Mr. E
episodes.overview: The wombats battle sea monsters, surfing scoundrels, and pointing rocks on their way to make a sandwich delivery.

episodes.name: Balloonie for Youie
episodes.overview: Mr. E buys a robot to hand out balloons.
